# Project 16 - Live Potrait using RPi
![Potrait](https://github.com/KJSashank/Task-1/blob/master/Project-16/Scary.gif)
## Description -
DIY jump scare portrait from scratch using Raspberry Pi 3 B, Python and AtmosFX Videos unliving portraits. It uses PIR sensor to detect motion nd then executes the video inorder to scare them on the LCD screen disguized as a potrait. It records the video of the surprised passersby via the RPi camera.
## Materials -
Raspberry Pi 3 Model B,	PIR Motion Sensor (generic), 19" LCD Monitor, Raspberry Pi Camera Module
### What I Learnt?
Acessing videos, setting a base image when the video doesnt play, usageof RPi Camera and PIR sensor.
